 Jesus is showing His disciples what the kingdom of God looks like

434
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:14,440
 by telling them who the king actually cares deeply about.

435
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:16,680
 You want to know what the kingdom of God looks like?

436
00:34:16,680 --> 00:34:21,720
 Jesus is saying, "I'm the king and I'm telling you who do I care the most about.

437
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:28,400
 The broken, the vulnerable, the oppressed, the hungry, the poor.

438
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:34,800
 Those are the people that I care the most about," Jesus says.

439
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:38,960
 Not the successful, not the influencers.

440
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:43,280
 While this world always think even when the Israelites were expecting,

441
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:45,560
 or the Jews were expecting the Messiah, they thought,

442
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:49,640
 "This guy must be strong, must be powerful, must come and fight the world."

443
00:34:49,640 --> 00:34:55,080
 But Jesus says, "I come here, my kingdom is different."

444
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:59,320
 And so, the poor in spirit.

445
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:01,880
 Yes, some of them could be really so poor,

446
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:06,560
 they lack the resources to meet their minimum living standard.

447
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:09,680
 But you know, sometimes we also lack the spiritual resources,

448
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,400
 the mental resources.

449
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,360
 We lack the character that is needed.

450
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:17,480
 We lack the love that is needed in a marriage, in a family.

451
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:23,440
 We lack the character, we lack the integrity that is needed in a workplace.

452
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:27,960
 We thought, "Oh yeah, I'm kind of a loving person, that's okay,"

453
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,960
 until you and your spouse get into the next fight.

454
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:34,680
 "Oh yeah, you know, I'm kind of an honest person,"

455
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:38,720
 until the temptation comes.

456
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:44,760
 Or until you have to tell a white lie to cover up something in your life.

457
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:50,840
 Only until we realize, we identify ourselves with those who are poor in spirit,

458
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:53,320
 Jesus says, "You know what? My kingdom is yours,

459
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:56,960
 and you will experience my kingdom there and then."

460
00:35:56,960 --> 00:36:00,760
 When you know you don't have enough in you,

461
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:03,520
 when you know you are the ones who are lacking,

462
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:10,800
 when you finally realize God's kingdom shows up for us there and then.

463
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:13,440
 The poor in spirit are the ones who are empty,

464
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:15,600
 the mourners are those who are broken,

465
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,240
 the meek are the powerless,

466
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:20,400
 and the hungry are those who are desperate.

467
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:23,400
 But God's kingdom is an upside-down kingdom.

468
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:27,080
 That's why when Jesus was declaring this message,

469
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:31,800
 it has something that we always describe in the vine like this,

470
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:34,920
 He's here to comfort the afflicted,

471
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:38,640
 but He's also here to afflict the comfortable.

472
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:41,200
 He is here to force us to look into ourselves,

473
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:45,040
 "Where does my security come from?

474
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:48,600
 Is it that number or many digits in my bank account,

475
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:55,920
 or the title or how many titles or suffix after your name in your name card?

476
00:36:55,920 --> 00:37:00,760
 What are the things that give you your security in life?"

477
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,720
 There are a few things we need to know.

478
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:07,960
 Beatitudes as good news to the suffering is not demands for righteousness.

479
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:13,240
 It exposes an implicit judgment on the comfortable, on the powerful,

480
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:21,080
 if those are the people that would exploit other people for their own interest.

481
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:22,760
 It clarifies repentance.

482
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:25,480
 It's not just, "Oh, I've done this or that."

483
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:30,120
 It's about realizing, "What? I don't have what it takes.

484
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:34,320
 I don't have what it takes to live this life that God has called me to live.

485
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,800
 I need Him."

486
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:41,480
 When you realize that, you will naturally proserkoma.

487
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,080
 You would come to Jesus.

488
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:46,240
 You know you don't have what it takes to live the kind of life

489
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,960
 that He has called you to live.

490
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:51,720
 You would want to come to Him, especially when you recognize

491
00:37:51,720 --> 00:37:54,800
 that's the teaching moment, that He's speaking to you.

492
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:58,120
 You would want to draw near to Him, not just for the proximity,

493
00:37:58,120 --> 00:37:59,040
 but in purpose.

494
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:00,280
 You want to listen.

495
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,480
 You want to obey.

496
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:04,560
 And you want His word to come and transform your life.

497
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:10,040
 And so, where do we find our security today?

498
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,720
 Where do we find our security?

499
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:16,880
 The amazing thing is that, you know, when Jesus declared all this,

500
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:20,120
 like He's the poor in spirit, the mourning.

501
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:23,760
 You know, for the poor in spirit, He's actually the generous God.

502
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:26,760
 For the mourning, He is the comforter.

503
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:31,440
 For those who are meek or powerless or lowly, He is their defender.

504
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:35,600
 For those who are hungry for righteousness, He is the righteous King.

505
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:39,480
 The answer to these people is Jesus Himself.

506
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:43,680
 So, the good news today is the King has come.

507
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:49,000
 So, when in the presence of the King, in His kingdom, these people,

508
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:55,120
 these people whom He cares about so deeply, they are blessed.

509
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:59,120
 So, the question is, where do we stand today?

510
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:02,920
 Do we still try to find security in the things that we used to find?

511
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:07,680
 Or do we come into the economy of this kingdom and align ourselves,

512
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:11,920
 first of all, and say, "Yeah, I thought I have, but actually I don't.

513
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:14,360
 I thought I'm rich, but actually I'm poor.

514
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,880
 I thought I'm strong, but actually I'm weak."

515
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:21,320
 Would we allow the Holy Spirit to come and transform our understanding

516
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:25,560
 of weak and strong, rich and poor, and allow Him to show us

517
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,920
 who we really are and what we really need?

518
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:32,600
 The moment we realize, "Wow, I'm actually poor," God says,

519
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:35,680
 "You know what? My kingdom is yours. I'm with you.

520
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:40,520
 I'm your king, and I care about you deeply."

521
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:44,840
 And I know I talk about the "not yet" of the kingdom in this church a lot.

522
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:48,440
 Like, the kingdom of God is something that is so far away,

523
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:52,960
 so we're still experiencing all the brokenness, all the hardship.

524
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:58,240
 We talk a lot about that, especially during, what was that in December?

525
00:39:58,240 --> 00:40:00,000
 Advent, yes, sorry, I forgot.

526
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:03,520
 We talk about it in Advent, but I want to talk about the alreadyness

527
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:05,720
 of the kingdom of God as well.

528
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:07,400
 The king is already here.

529
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,080
 Jesus has already arrived.

530
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:11,880
 He has already done something in your life, in my life.

531
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:15,840
 What we should see should be the alreadyness of the kingdom

532
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,880
 in this church, in our lives.

533
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:22,040
 There was one time the staff with one child were on a retreat,

534
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:27,200
 and I was in a very super cold, kind of air-conditioned room.

535
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:30,960
 I was just walking and praying, and suddenly I walked to the door,

536
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:35,600
 which was open, and it was a very hot, sunny day outside.

537
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:39,800
 When I walked towards the door, when I approached the door,

538
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:43,080
 wow, so warm.

539
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:46,720
 I experienced the warmth of the sun outside,

540
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:51,800
 but at the same time, I could still feel the cold in the room at the same time.

541
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:57,200
 I experienced both, but I'm starting to experience the warmth,

542
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:59,640
 the already and the not yet.

543
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:00,760
 And you know what?

544
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:05,480
 For us, for God, for His kingdom to continue to grow,

545
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:08,160
 He's just asking you and me to be those doors,

546
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:11,800
 doors in your family, in your workplace, in your community.

547
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:16,800
 When you're that open door, when you're that connect point, that hotspot,

548
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:20,360
 people around you, they will start to experience the kingdom,

549
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:24,760
 the comfort, the warmth, the energy, the joy, the peace, the love.

550
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:29,080
 They will start to be that door, be that connection point for them,

551
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:31,360
 because the kingdom has already come.

552
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:35,640
 Are we just selling people something that is so far away

553
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:38,680
 because we barely come to Jesus ourselves,

554
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:41,680
 or are we going to actually take those steps every day

555
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:45,480
 to prostrate our mind to Jesus so that His life is overflowing in us,

556
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:48,600
 and we will become those doors in our community, in our city,

557
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:53,000
 that the kingdom, the reality of the kingdom would expand

558
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:57,440
 and invade our surroundings through you and me?

559
00:41:57,440 --> 00:42:00,320
 Are we going to be that kind of church?

560
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:03,800
 I think that's the question we're asking here today.

561
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:07,000
 So why don't we spend some time to pray together?

562
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:23,160
 Father, thank you that your kingdom is near.

563
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:25,280
 The king is here.

564
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:27,240
 You're not someone who is so far away.

565
00:42:27,240 --> 00:42:31,480
 You're even present right now in this room.

566
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:37,280
 It's your very presence that we sense in a time of worship.

567
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:39,600
 It was your presence, it was your goodness,

568
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:42,360
 it was your kingdom at work in the testimony

569
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:45,680
 we had the privilege to listen to earlier,

570
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:50,600
 and to submit our lives to you to prose Erkomai,

571
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:53,320
 to come to you so that we, ourselves,

572
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:56,280
 will be able to tell that kind of stories as well.

573
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:59,640
 And also not just ourselves, so that people around us

574
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:03,120
 will be able to tell that kind of stories as well.

575
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:07,920
 Father, I pray a very simple prayer for our church, for this church,

576
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:10,680
 that God, I pray that in this church,

577
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:14,800
 there will be disciples and not just crowds.

578
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:18,800
 I pray that when you are in the posture of authority,

579
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,240
 when you're about to speak,

580
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:25,040
 we would come to you with intentional listening.

581
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:27,240
 We would come to you in a posture and say,

582
00:43:27,240 --> 00:43:31,920
 "God, please come and transform me with your word in my life."

583
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:36,080
 And God, I pray that discipleship in this church would look like this.

584
00:43:36,080 --> 00:43:39,160
 As we prose Erkomai, as we draw near you,

585
00:43:39,160 --> 00:43:40,800
 as you change our lives,

586
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:44,440
 we would become those doorways

587
00:43:44,440 --> 00:43:47,400
 that unleash your kingdom in this world.

588
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:51,840
 That's what the discipleship of this church is about.

589
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:54,880
 It's about our lives aligning with you

590
00:43:54,880 --> 00:43:57,960
 so that the king can send his representatives,

591
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:01,800
 his ambassadors into Hong Kong, into Yuen Long, into this world,

592
00:44:01,800 --> 00:44:05,040
 that this world will be transformed by your kingdom.

593
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:06,480
 We are your ambassador.

594
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:09,680
 We're here to announce that, yes, the king has come.

595
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:11,200
 The kingdom is at hand.

596
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:13,800
 We would see it in families around us.

597
00:44:13,800 --> 00:44:15,200
 We'll see it in workplaces.

598
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:18,320
 We'll see it in all those people's lives around us.

599
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:20,960
 God, this is our declaration.

600
00:44:20,960 --> 00:44:23,760
 And we thank you, Lord.

601
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:27,560
 We thank you, Lord.

602
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:29,920
 You show us what your kingdom is like

603
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:37,800
 by revealing, by sharing with us who the king cares about.

604
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:41,080
 I love this king.

605
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:45,640
 I have so much joy inside of me just talking about this king.

606
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:48,120
 He's such a good king.

607
00:44:48,120 --> 00:44:51,200
 He's so trustworthy.

608
00:44:51,200 --> 00:44:53,200
 And it's time to put our trust in him

609
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:57,840
 over all the other things we have put our trust in.

610
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:00,400
 Why don't we stand, church?

611
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:03,440
 Why don't we respond to his faithfulness, his love?

612
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:06,080
 He said his kingdom is here already.

613
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:08,440
 Why don't we just take the step to him and say,

614
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:10,480
 I want to be a part of that kingdom,

615
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:14,080
 And I want to bring this kingdom forward in Jesus' name.

